The paper discusses graphical models and their use in solving combinatorial optimization problems through message passing. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the use of graphical models, discrete mathematics (cs.DM) for the study of combinatorial problems, machine learning (cs.LG) for the use of message passing algorithms, systems and control (cs.SY) for the analysis of complex systems, and information theory (cs.IT) for the study of inference and approximation algorithms.
